                  </persName>
            . I am warehouse-keeper in the London-docks; in August, 1828, Willis applied to me for employment as a labourer, and said he was much distressed - he continued there, from the 8th of August, off and on, till the 17th of January, 1829, at 2s. 6d. a day.</p>
